name: electrified-armor-laboratory-eal
notes: The EAL develops technologies and methods to advance pulse power based armor components, subsystems and systems; investigates and analyzes new adaptive armor technologies; and provides depot-level nondestructive evaluation (NDE) of various types of vehicle armor structural health, real-time assessment of armor using optical and ultrasonic embedded sensors.  Capabilities: EAL research can be applied to any system requiring pulse power systems and electro-mechanical features. Low voltage electromechanical actuator (EMA) control system testing, high-voltage bench top testing is expected in FY15. For in-house NDE, the lab has ultrasonic transducer characterization equipment, infrared imaging, a millimeter wave imaging table and a nanoelectronic, spintronic and metamaterials testing station.  Benefits:  &#8226;&#8194; Electrified armor protection to defeat threats at reduced weight. &#8226;&#8194; Adaptive armor to integrate multiple armor technologies, increasing protection at a reduced weight. &#8226;&#8194; Real-time health monitoring of opaque or transparent armor without detaching the armor from the vehicle. &#8226;&#8194; Armor-embedded radio communications to protect antenna from damage and conceal mission purpose. &#8226;&#8194; Embedded radar detection and microwave energy harvesting on the battlefield.
title: Electrified Armor Laboratory (EAL)
